🤍Fail, Learn, Try Again 🌟 All I hear lately is, “Mom, please stop with the life lessons.” It’s a delicate balance of trying to usher them in the right direction, but also knowing when to step back so they realize they already have everything they need within themselves. 💪🏽 It’s a delicate balance of loving and pushing them at the same time. 💕 I’m so in awe of the little people in my life.  How much they’ve grown in the last few years despite whatever challenges or disappointments they’ve faced.  Just by watching them, they’re showing me what real growth looks like.  Sometimes, the youngest ones in our lives can open our hearts with the best wisdom 🤍🙏🏽 #growth #children #daughter #love #family #dance #weekend #grateful #blessed #momlife #joy #proud

Today is hard.⁠
⁠
Dropping the kids off at school, once again wondering if they are safe in a place that is supposed to be a haven, to nurture and support and care for them when we are away. ⁠
⁠
Yet again, having to have the same tough conversation with my big kids as we pull up to their school and police are there (which I’m SO thankful for) at the building. Worrying about my little ones who don’t yet understand, yet are still affected in so many ways💔.⁠
⁠
As a mother and as a parent, my heart is with the MSU community and everyone that has been affected by this horrific tragedy. I’m thinking of and praying so hard for the moms just like me that have lost everything because of a senseless act, made even more devastating by the fact that - yet again - it’s right in our own backyard.⁠
⁠
There are no words, right now. Just support and prayers.⁠

🩷This is a community of warriors. There’s strength in numbers.
